DataElement.preferredDefinition: an indicator of the modification of the use of chemical substances that are used to stain and color leakage in the resinous material applied to the occlusal surfaces of posterior teeth to prevent occlusal decay by filling in the fissures and/or crevices of the tooth.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Chemical substances that are used to stain and color other materials. The coloring may or may not be permanent. Dyes can also be used as therapeutic agents and test reagents in medicine and scientific research.

Concepts.definition: Agents used to enhance the color or contrast of target materials or samples. Dyes have some affinity for their substrates and are usually applied in a solution.
